# ğŸš€ **More Deployment Commands (With Clear Meaning + Examples)**

---

## **1ï¸âƒ£ Check all Deployments**

### **Command**

```
kubectl get deployments
```

### **Meaning**

Cluster me jitne deployments chal rahe hain unki list.

### **Example**

You want to confirm your app is deployed â†’ run it.

---

## **2ï¸âƒ£ Describe a Deployment**

### **Command**

```
kubectl describe deployment <deployment-name>
```

### **Meaning**

Deployment ka full detail â€” events, errors, image kaun sa use ho raha hai, rollout status, etc.

### **Example**

```
kubectl describe deployment myapp-deploy
```

---

## **3ï¸âƒ£ Update Deployment Image**

(Real interview me bohot poochte hain)

### **Command**

```
kubectl set image deployment/myapp-deploy nginx=nginx:latest
```

### **Meaning**

Deployment ke containers ka image change karna.

---

## **4ï¸âƒ£ Scale Deployment**

### **Command**

```
kubectl scale deployment myapp-deploy --replicas=5
```

### **Meaning**

Pods ko badhana/ghatana.

---

## **5ï¸âƒ£ Check Rollout Status**

### **Command**

```
kubectl rollout status deployment/myapp-deploy
```

### **Meaning**

New version deploy hua kya? Success ya stuck?

---

## **6ï¸âƒ£ Rollback to Previous Version**

### **Command**

```
kubectl rollout undo deployment/myapp-deploy
```

### **Meaning**

Agar new deployment me error aa gaya â†’ previous version par jao.

---

## **7ï¸âƒ£ View Deployment History**

### **Command**

```
kubectl rollout history deployment/myapp-deploy
```

### **Meaning**

Deployment ke purane revisions dekhna.

---

## **8ï¸âƒ£ Apply Deployment From YAML File**

### **Command**

```
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
```

### **Meaning**

YAML file me jo changes kiye â†’ cluster me apply karo.

---

## **9ï¸âƒ£ Delete Deployment**

### **Command**

```
kubectl delete deployment myapp-deploy
```

### **Meaning**

Deployment + uske pods sab delete ho jayenge.

---

## **ğŸ”Ÿ Dry-Run Deployment (Check Before Apply)**

### **Command**

```
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml --dry-run=client
```

### **Meaning**

File sahih hai ya nahi â†’ apply nahi hoga, bas check hoga.

